Destinations

Popular Vacation Destinations

Caribbean

You can explore the Caribbean islands on a luxurious cruise ship, rent a Villa or stay at an All-Inclusive resort on a magnificent beach. Some of the most popular Caribbean islands our customers travel to include Dominican Republic, Jamaica, Aruba and The Bahamas.

Americas

America offers a variety of cultures, cuisines, landscapes, history and adventures. Known as the “melting-pot” of the Western Hemisphere, this is a continent overflowing with activities and sights – allowing you to focus your travels to what interests you the most.

Asia

Asia, the world’s largest and most populous continent, has many offerings for every traveler, whether you are looking to check something off of your bucket list or need some serious relaxation. From the bustling mega cities of Tokyo, Beijing and Shanghai to the white sand beaches in the Southeast Asia, the options are endless when you choose to travel Asia. If you have ever wanted to visit Asia, now is the perfect time.

Africa

Our African tours showcase the continent's biodiversity, which ranges from the Sahara desert to tropical jungle, from snow-capped volcanic Mount Kilimanjaro to the beaches of East and West Africa, may be its greatest asset. There is the excitement of stalking big game in the African bush, the thrill of whitewater rafting through the gorges below Victoria Falls, and the awe of seeing the Egyptian pyramids at sunrise. plexes that take advantage of game parks, golf courses, beaches and beautiful scenery.

Europe

Europe consists of timeless landscapes, quiet country roads, poppy fields, and stone farmhouses encircled by elegant cypresses. Discover treasures of medieval villages perched on hillsides cloaked with dark forests hiding truffle secrets. Listen to fountains splash in sunny squares or waves sweeping the shore. Walk along old pilgrimage routes past roadside crosses and tiny chapels or follow in artists’ footsteps by seeing where they created their masterpieces and the museums that now protect those works. With so many cultural influences over the past centuries, Europe has become a vacation spot that never disappoints.

Middle East

The Middle East has so many highlights it is difficult to know where to begin. Visit the atmospheric souk of Aleppo and the ancient city of Damascus, the beautiful hidden mountain monastery of Mar Moussa and a stunning desert palace. For the more active, there is time to swim – or float – in the Dead Sea, snorkel over the coral reefs of the Red Sea, and take a 4WD into the amazing landscape of Wadi Rum and spend a night under the stars. The highlight of any vacation is likely to be the magnificent tastes, as the drinking and eating are world-renowned.
